## Scenes & startup flow

| Order | Scene | Notes |
|-------|--------|--------|
| 0 | `Assets/Chorewars/Scenes/Bootstrap.unity` | Entry; YAML historically **empty of GameObjects** (nav/lighting shell only). |
| 1 | `HooverMode.unity` | Routed from Bootstrap via `BootstrapSceneRouter`. |
| 2 | `MowingMode.unity` | In build list; optional. |

- **`BootstrapSceneRouter`** (`Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Core/BootstrapSceneRouter.cs`): On `AfterSceneLoad`, if active scene is `Bootstrap`, loads last mode (default `HooverMode`).  
- **`QuestXrRigBootstrap`** (`Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Bootstrap/QuestXrRigBootstrap.cs`): `BeforeSceneLoad` builds **XROrigin + tracked Main Camera** (or fallback camera), `DontDestroyOnLoad`, so empty scenes still have something to render. Log prefix: **`BoreDoom/Startup`**.  
- **`XrHeadsetDiagnostics`** (`Assets/Chorewars/Scripts/Diagnostics/`): One-time **`XRDisplaySubsystem`** check + **`TelemetryLogger`** + **`SubsystemHealth.XrDisplay`**.

---

## XR / Quest (critical)

1. **XR Plug-in Management** must reference real assets — `Assets/Editor/BoreDoomXrManagementBootstrap.cs` creates/registers **OpenXR loader** and links **XRGeneralSettingsPerBuildTarget** under `Assets/XR/` when missing.  
2. **OpenXR on Quest requires Meta Quest Support** (and Unity docs recommend **Oculus Touch Controller Profile**) for **Android** — loader alone is insufficient; features are enabled in the same Editor bootstrap (`EnableQuestOpenXrAndroidFeatures`).  
3. After pulling, **open Unity once** so bootstrap runs; then rebuild Android so manifest/OpenXR metadata stay consistent.  
4. **Graphics:** Built-in RP (`GraphicsSettings` — no custom SRP asset). Android targets **Vulkan** for Quest.

