## Debugging on device

- Unity tag: `adb logcat -s Unity`  
- Filter (Windows): `findstr /I "BoreDoom Startup XRDisplaySubsystem Exception Error"`  
- **`MQ3.log`:** JSON lines under `Application.persistentDataPath` — see `docs/quest3-build.md` for `adb pull`.  
- Watch for **`BoreDoom/Startup`** and **`XRDisplaySubsystem … running=True`**. If `running=False` or count `0`, XR subsystems did not start — verify OpenXR Android features in Project Settings and reinstall APK built after Editor bootstrap.

---

## On-device telemetry (implemented)

- **`Chorewars.Diagnostics.TelemetryLogger`** writes JSON lines to **`Application.persistentDataPath/MQ3.log`** (~10 MB rotation to `MQ3.1.log`). Used by bootstrap, router, and XR diagnostics.  
- **`SubsystemHealth`** holds coarse statuses (`NotStarted` / `Initialising` / `Ok` / `Failed`) for XR display, bootstrap rig, passthrough, HUD, etc. — bootstrap + XR display updated today; extend as features ship.

